@baseUrl = http://localhost:5207
@receptionistId = 1
@securityId = 2
@adminId = 3

### ---------------------------------
### Users / Actors Setup
### ---------------------------------
### NOTE:
### The current backend requires user IDs in visit actions:
### - createdById
### - approvedById
### - checkedInById
### - checkedOutById
### But there are NO /api/users endpoints implemented yet.
### So these IDs must already exist in the database.
### Expected mock/demo IDs used by the frontend and HTTP file:
### - Receptionist -> 1
### - Security     -> 2
### - Admin        -> 3
###
### If your DB does not contain these users, visit create/approve/check-in/check-out will fail.
### Once UsersController exists, replace this section with real POST /api/users calls.

### Users - Expected demo actor ids
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/visits
Accept: application/json

### ---------------------------------
### Visitors
### ---------------------------------

### Visitors - Get all
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/visitors
Accept: application/json

###

### Visitors - Get by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/visitors/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Visitors - Create
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/visitors
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Jane Visitor",
  "phone": "0799993999",
  "nationalId": "NIDA-123456782",
  "company": "Acme Logistics",
  "vehiclePlate": "T123ABC",
  "photoUrl": "https://example.com/photos/jane-visitor.jpg"
}

###

### Visitors - Update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/visitors/1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Jane Visitor Updated",
  "phone": "0788888888",
  "nationalId": "NIDA-987654321",
  "company": "Acme Logistics",
  "vehiclePlate": "T456DEF",
  "photoUrl": "https://example.com/photos/jane-visitor-updated.jpg"
}

###

### Visitors - Delete
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/visitors/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Visitors - Get all visits for one visitor
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/visitors/1/visits
Accept: application/json

### ---------------------------------
### Offices
### ---------------------------------

### Offices - Get all
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/offices
Accept: application/json

###

### Offices - Get by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/offices/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Offices - Create
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/offices
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Records Office",
  "floor": "First Floor",
  "officeCode": "REC-01"
}

###

### Offices - Update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/offices/1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Records Office Updated",
  "floor": "Second Floor",
  "officeCode": "REC-02"
}

###

### Offices - Delete
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/offices/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Offices - Get all visits for one office
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/offices/1/visits
Accept: application/json

### ---------------------------------
### Departments
### ---------------------------------

### Departments - Get all
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/departments
Accept: application/json

###

### Departments - Get by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/departments/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Departments - Get by office
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/departments/office/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Departments - Create
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/departments
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Reception",
  "description": "Front desk and guest handling",
  "officeId": 1
}

###

### Departments - Update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/departments/1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Reception Updated",
  "description": "Front desk, guest handling and bookings",
  "officeId": 1
}

###

### Departments - Delete
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/departments/1
Accept: application/json

### ---------------------------------
### Visits
### ---------------------------------

### Visits - Get all
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/visits
Accept: application/json

###

### Visits - Get by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/visits/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Visits - Create (starts as Pending, requires existing user id)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/visits
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "visitorId": 1,
  "officeId": 1,
  "createdById": {{receptionistId}},
  "visitDate": "2026-07-29T10:00:00Z",
  "expectedArrival": "2026-06-29T09:45:00Z",
  "purpose": "Intern follow-up",
  "attachmentUrl": "https://example.com/files/invitation.pdf"
}

###

### Visits - Approve (requires existing user id)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/visits/1/approve
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "approvedById": {{receptionistId}}
}

###

### Visits - Reject (requires existing user id)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/visits/1/reject
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "approvedById": {{receptionistId}}
}

###

### Visits - Check in (requires existing user id)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/visits/1/checkin
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "checkedInById": {{securityId}},
  "gate": "Main Gate",
  "badgeNumber": "BG-001"
}

###

### Visits - Check out (requires existing user id)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/visits/1/checkout
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "checkedOutById": {{securityId}},
  "remarks": "Visitor exited successfully"
}

### ---------------------------------
### Parking Slots
### ---------------------------------

### Parking Slots - Get all
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/parkingslots
Accept: application/json

###

### Parking Slots - Get by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/parkingslots/1
Accept: application/json

###

### Parking Slots - Create
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/parkingslots
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "code": "A-01",
  "zone": "Zone A",
  "status": 1
}

###

### Parking Slots - Update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/parkingslots/1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "code": "A-01",
  "zone": "Zone A",
  "status": 2
}

###

### Parking Slots - Delete
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/parkingslots/1
Accept: application/json

